<item>
            <title>[SPARK-38916] Tasks not killed caused by race conditions between killTask() and launchTask()</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-38916</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Sometimes when the scheduler tries to cancel a task right after it launches that task on the executor, the KillTask and LaunchTask events can come in a reversed order, causing the task to escape the kill-task signal and finish &quot;secretly&quot;. And those tasks even show as an un-launched task in Spark UI.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
